    "body": "### Neovim version (nvim -v)\n\nv0.8.0-dev+9-g1facad234\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nn/a\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nLinux\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nHappens in both alacritty (latest) and kitty (latest)\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\ntmux-256color, xterm-kitty\n\n### Installation\n\nAUR: neovim-git\n\n### How to reproduce the issue\n\n1. `nvim --clean`\r\n2. `:lua vim.api.nvim_win_set_option(vim.api.nvim_open_win(vim.api.nvim_create_buf(false, true), false, { relative = \"editor\", width = 1, height = 1, row = 1, col = 1 }), \"winhighlight\", \"Normal:Search\")`\r\n3. `:copen`\r\n\n\n### Expected behavior\n\n![2022-04-27_02-27-52_Alacritty](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/21299126/165487729-be1776e2-6b6e-456f-8302-b5a90d5a4f05.png)\r\n\r\nFocus quickfix window, `:echo &winhighlight` should be blank\n\n### Actual behavior\n\n![2022-04-27_02-27-03_Alacritty](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/21299126/165487574-e0016132-e2b1-4ea7-8874-0ab5040b00d6.png)\r\n\r\nFocus quickfix window, `:echo &winhighlight` is `Normal:Search`\r\n\r\nAlso happens with loclist window.",
